abstract: Mr. Castro, the former housing secretary and mayor of San Antonio, was the only Latino candidate in the race. He championed progressive policies but did not find his footing in polls.
snippet: Mr. Castro, the former housing secretary and mayor of San Antonio, was the only Latino candidate in the race. He championed progressive policies but did not find his footing in polls.
lead_paragraph: Julián Castro, the former housing secretary who was the only Latino candidate in the Democratic primary, said Thursday he would end his bid for the presidency, capping a yearlong campaign where he struggled in polls but remained a policy pacesetter on immigration and fighting poverty.

abstract: He’s a bad show, but it’s not low-flow.
snippet: He’s a bad show, but it’s not low-flow.
lead_paragraph: We’re now officially trudging through the new year. (And good luck on that healthier-living resolution.) This is when we adjust to the fact that nothing has changed. You weren’t allowed to toss Donald Trump out with the old. Although it would have been nice if he’d at least have stayed quiet until all of the Christmas trees were down.

abstract: This year saw 13 Democratic candidates and one Republican drop out. Our photographers captured them on the campaign trail. As 2019 ends, here’s a look back.
snippet: This year saw 13 Democratic candidates and one Republican drop out. Our photographers captured them on the campaign trail. As 2019 ends, here’s a look back.
lead_paragraph: Some candidates were in for just a few months; others for almost the entire year. One left the race before most others even entered it. And now, at the end of 2019, a historically large field of presidential contenders has shrunk from more than two dozen to a slightly more manageable group of 18.

abstract: Automakers and suppliers are cutting costs so they can invest in new technology. Workers are feeling the impact.
snippet: Automakers and suppliers are cutting costs so they can invest in new technology. Workers are feeling the impact.
lead_paragraph: ÖHRINGEN, Germany — Öhringen lies deep in automaking country, homeland of Germany’s biggest industry and a source of national pride. And by most appearances, life is pretty good.

abstract: A voter asked Joseph R. Biden Jr. if he’d consider choosing a Republican as his running mate. “I would, but I can’t think of one now,” Mr. Biden responded.
snippet: A voter asked Joseph R. Biden Jr. if he’d consider choosing a Republican as his running mate. “I would, but I can’t think of one now,” Mr. Biden responded.
lead_paragraph: EXETER, N.H. — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. is accustomed to fielding questions from voters about picking a running mate. But on Monday, he was asked a particularly provocative one: Would he consider choosing a Republican as his vice president?

abstract: An early look at fourth-quarter fund-raising shows Joseph R. Biden Jr. bouncing back, Elizabeth Warren lagging her previous benchmark and Bernie Sanders continuing to haul in cash.
snippet: An early look at fourth-quarter fund-raising shows Joseph R. Biden Jr. bouncing back, Elizabeth Warren lagging her previous benchmark and Bernie Sanders continuing to haul in cash.
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren’s slip in the 2020 primary polls has been accompanied by a dip in donations, with her campaign setting a rare public goal: aiming to raise $20 million for the fourth quarter of 2019 ending Tuesday, or about 20 percent less than what she raised in the previous three-month period.
